Broadbent Was ‘Reasonably Close’ to Voting for QE This Month

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   R y a n
-- 
2011-09-26T09:42:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/broadbent-was-reasonably-close-to-voting-for-qe-this-month.html
Bank of England  official maker Ben
Broadbent said he was “reasonably close” to voting for more
bond purchases at this month’s policy meeting.  Broadbent made the comments to reporters in  London  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer Ryan in London at 
